-- S&P math on U.S. downgrade off by trillions: CNBC
-- 
-- Fri Aug 5, 2011 7:58pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/08/05/us-usa-debt-downgrade-idUSTRE7746VF20110805

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Standard & Poor's calculations on a possible downgrade of U.S. credit ratings were off by "trillions," CNBC quoted sources as saying on Friday. 

 CNBC and ABC News both reported on Friday that the U.S. government is bracing for a possible downgrade of its AAA credit rating by S&P. (Reporting by  Walter Brandimarte ; Editing by  Jan Paschal )